title: Desargues' theorem

Let $$A,A',B,B',C,C'$$ be points in a [[projective plane|Projective subspace]], $$A\ne A',\ B\ne B',\ C\ne C'.$$ If the lines $$AA',BB',CC'$$ intersect in one point $$P,$$ then the intersection points

$$
A''=BC\cap B'C',\quad B''=AC\cap A'C',\quad C''=AB\cap A'B'
$$

lie on one line.

The converse is also true.